news.title: Over 50% rise in property tax collection in Ahmedabad
news.para: As per Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation’s (AMC) statement, the tax department collected Rs 328.42 crore in property tax this year against Rs 218.17 crore in the same period last year.

news.title: Kolkata: More Bowbazar buildings in zone of uncertainty
news.para: The team of experts from Jadavpur University, appointed by KMC to assess the affected buildings on Durga Pithuri Lane and the serpentine lanes off B B Ganguly Street have been visiting the site since Monday to ascertain the extent of damage suffered due to last Wednesday’s subsidence at the Metro construction site.

news.title: Gurugram: Why some residents are paying lakhs for new power connection
news.para: Of the over Rs 317 crore that the 13 private developers collectively owe to DHBVN for having failed to provide the much-needed power infrastructure in these 16 plotted colonies and 32 housing societies developed by them.

news.title: PayPal renews lease for India headquarters in Futura Tech Parks in Chennai
news.para: Futura Tech Park is part of the portfolio of X Office Parks India, an office property platform sponsored by the global private equity real estate firm. Through this lease renewal, PayPal will get access to 2.6 lakh sq ft of space.

news.title: Bombay HC issues contempt notice to builder for not paying Rs 1.3 crore rent arrears
news.para: ​The order on May 4 was passed on a petition by Satguru CHSL against Sai Tasveer Developers and its four partners, who are couples - Jayesh and Heena Tanna, Kamal and Rita Thakkar - alleging non-compliance of undertakings given to a sole arbitrator.

news.title: Rustomjee Group company plans Rs 1,000-crore IPO
news.para: The company has recently raised ₹170 crore through pre-IPO placement. The deal, according to the bankers, comprised 100% primary infusion and witnessed participation from HDFC Capital, IIFL Group, and the family office of Jagdish Master.

news.title: UP RERA authorises promoter of Vasundhara Grand to complete stuck project
news.para: This is 13th real estate project under rehabilitation to achieve completion under section – 8 of the RERA Act. ​The decision is as per the consent provided by the association of the allottees.

news.title: Mumbai: Adani Group company takes over Rs 5,000 crore project on RTO land
news.para: The firm has taken a majority stake and will jointly develop the over 11 lakh sq ft sale component of the project with developer Shiv Infra Vision, which had bagged the work in 2018.

news.title: U.S. housing market cooling as building permits tumble, starts fall
news.para: Homebuilding was already being constrained by soaring prices as well as shortages of materials. The housing market is the sector of the economy most sensitive to interest rates, with building permits a leading indicator for the sector.

news.title: Lucknow development body takes back 14 acre green belt from hotel
news.para: “On completion of the lease period and alleged violation of lease terms by the hotel management, LDA vice-chairman Akshay Tripathi cancelled the allotment of the land,” read the LDA statement.

news.title: China: New home prices fall in April for the first time since Dec as Covid bites
news.para: Average new-home prices in 70 major cities fell 0.2% on a month-on-month basis, compared with zero growth in March, according to Reuters calculations based on April data from the National Bureau of Statistics (NBS).

news.title: Encroachment upon railway land: Uttarakhand HC asks for property documents
news.para: ​After hearing the matter, the division bench of Justice Sarad Kumar Sharma and Justice RC Khulbe asked residents of the colony to present all their property documents within two weeks when the case will next be heard.

news.title: Indore: Building permission of 16 units in Pragati Green Colony revoked
news.para: According to IMC commissioner Pratibha Pal, the decision to revoke the building permission of 16 under-construction structures in Pragati Green Colony under ward 76 of zone 19 was taken for violating set approvals.

news.title: Ajmera Realty's profit at Rs 14 crore in Q4 FY22
news.para: Total income rose to Rs 183.62 crore in the fourth quarter of the last fiscal year from Rs 79.78 crore in the year-ago period, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: Hundreds rendered homeless as BDA razes houses in Bareilly
news.para: ​​As per BDA officials, there are around 500 houses built on "4 hectare of illegally sold land" in Chandpur and Doharia villages on the outskirts of Bareilly, and all of them are under scanner now.
